title: ACC Power Poll: Trap game for Clemson with FSU looming?
text:
ACC Power Poll: Trap game for Clemson with FSU looming? 
By Garry Smits Wed, Oct 21, 2015 @ 6:35 pm | updated Wed, Oct 21, 2015 @ 9:24 pm Photos AP Clemson quarterback Deshaun Watson (4) throws a pass against Boston College during the second half of an NCAA college football game, Saturday, Oct. 17, 2015, in Clemson, S.C. 
ACC POWER POLL 
Playing at Miami is the trap game before facing the Seminoles in two weeks. 
2. FLORIDA STATE (6-0) 
Paul Johnson’s Tech teams drive ’Noles batty: 300 yards rushing, 32.5 points per game in four meetings. 
3. PITTSBURGH (5-1) 
In only 31 games, WR Tyler Boyd has moved to the top of team’s career receiving list with 204 catches. 
4. DUKE (5-1) 
Blue Devils play four of their last six games on the road, beginning with this week’s short trek to Blacksburg. 
5. NORTH CAROLINA (5-1) 
Offense is purring like a high-end sports car. And the defense is steadily improving. 
6. MIAMI (4-2) 
QB Brad Kaaya hasn’t thrown an interception in an ACC game this season and has only one overall. 
7. LOUISVILLE (2-4) 
Schedule is favorable for a late fall run to bowl eligibility. 
8. VIRGINIA TECH (3-4) 
Most-penalized team in the ACC and special teams so-so. That’s not Beamer Ball. 
9. GEORGIA TECH (2-5) 
Looks pretty hopeless against the Seminoles but at least got its run game going in loss to Pitt. 
10. N.C. STATE (4-2) 
Only Virginia has gained more turnovers than the Wolfpack’s measly five. 
11. VIRGINIA (2-4) 
Prior to beating Syracuse, had not scored 44 or more in an ACC game since routing Miami 48-0 in 2007. 
12. WAKE FOREST (3-4) 
Took a giant step backward by giving up 50 points, 538 yards to Tar Heels. 
13. SYRACUSE (3-3) 
Really needed that win against Virginia before facing Pitt, FSU, Louisville, Clemson in succession. 
14. BOSTON COLLEGE (3-4) 
Repeat after me: Defense does not win games. Defense keeps you in the game until the offense wins it. 
Garry Smits The Times-Union
